	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				This IMHO still need much work.<BR>
<BR>
First let me state that I am a 36 Paly on a pk server so my views are going to be exactly that MY views.  Having said that, let me begin.<BR>
<BR>
I think that ALL classes should be able to bind equally in all areas.  ie-melee and hybrids should be able to bind wherever casters do<BR>
<BR>
qualify statement- I do NOT think we should be able to get bind spells by no means (that is a caster area of specialty) BUT think on this...<BR>
consider how large the world of EQ is.  Also consider how much hybrids and specifically melee classes or dependent on their equipment.  When we die, we rez totally naked and vulnerable to the world (mobs AND pkers)at a bind point sometimes VERY far away.  For us to be combat effective, our gear is often our lifeline and going to do a corpse run is often time too much wasted on traveling.  Also, consider how many melee/hybrids DARE to venture too far away from their bind point to solo.  Probably not too many.  Soloing has always been much easier for casters (not wanting a change there) but being able to bind only in certain locations has really hamstrung melee classes in that area.  Unless we are grouped, who really wants to venture far into the outreaches only to risk death and xp loss for a possibly long walk back without a means to defend ourselves, probably not too many.  Allowing binds in any area will allow melee classes to be more viable as a character option while neither eliminating nor threatening the need for caster classes as group mates or binders.<BR>
<BR>
IMHO melee/hybrids are unfairly hamstrung when it comes to binds.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
